5)<\/li>\n<li>sequencing to confirm (~$4-6)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p>Overall, probably >$20 a mutant all in 2-3 days of waiting.<\/p>\n\n<p>(edit) I'm going with quikchange rather than OE-PCR simply because it removes the cloning steps. You will potentially need to screen more colonies with conventional cloning vs. quikchange.<\/p>\n","answer_id":1255,"question_id":1254,"up_vote_count":7,"last_edit_date":1330548127},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/dbe760221f32f95b2929618a8e23ec84?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":204,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/204/amy","reputation":1824,"display_name":"Amy"},"score":8,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/dbe760221f32f95b2929618a8e23ec84?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":204,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/204/amy","reputation":1824,"display_name":"Amy"},"score":2,"post_id":1258,"edited":false,"creation_date":1330545106,"comment_id":1519,"body":"I recently made 6 different constructs (single and double mutants) using overlap extension PCR. It took me one week, including sequence verification AND was a fraction of the cost for a quickchange kit."},{"owner":{"user_type":"does_not_exist","display_name":"user560"},"score":0,"post_id":1258,"edited":false,"creation_date":1330547410,"comment_id":1520,"body":"OE-PCR might be a good way to go too. I&#39;ll have to work out the primers that I would need.  I&#39;m aware of the uses of alanine scanning and conservative substitutions, but for my purposes these amino acids are in an unstructured region, at the C-terminus and deletion will tell me more information about the localization of the protein rather than function."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/222b478bab6d59dc5de514a87dba88cd?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":389,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/389/bobthejoe","r