57,"comment_id":1312,"body":"And after I&#39;ve stained the gel, I just pour it back into the container. I&#39;ve used the same bottle of stain for 2+ years. Works like a charm."}],"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date":1329539502,"creation_date":1329539502,"body":"<p>Since there's a lot of methanol in Coomassie stain, a significant amount would probably evaporate off each time you microwave it. Therefore, it'd be probably a good idea not to reuse it because (1) you're losing methanol, and (2) the concentration of everything else is thrown off.<\/p>\n\n<p>Why do you boil the stain? I just pour mine at RT right on the gel and it works fine.<\/p>\n","answer_id":1088,"question_id":1086,"up_vote_count":4}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/1086/how-often-can-you-reuse-coomassie-stain","last_activity_date":1329539502,"creation_date":1329531361,"answer_count":1,"title":"How often can you reuse coomassie stain?","body":"<p>I usually heat to boil in the microwave, and stain for 12 minutes. How often can I reuse this buffer?<\/p>\n","question_id":1086,"tags":["gel-electrophoresis"],"score":3,"accepted_answer_id":1088,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":743,"up_vote_count":3},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/6b73f0c4b971e2dde7147920e329fe7f?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":210,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/210/rob-ocallahan","reputation":81,"display_name":"Rob O'Callahan"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/28b0c2645da6a61f949db6196e52c567?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":184,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/184/thomas-ingalls","reputation":1306,"display_name":"Thomas Ingalls"},"score":0,"post_id":279,"edited":false,"creation_date":1324526026,"comment_id":291,"body":"Rob: can this question be answered by Google?  If it can, please come back and post an answer to your question.  Here&#39;s a hint: <a